article_title: Scooters Spark Fight in Evansville, Indiana
article_text:
EVANSVILLE, Ind.—With engines designed to putter along under 25 miles an hour, it's hard to imagine low-powered scooters as much of a menace to society. But as their numbers have multiplied in this Farm Belt river city, they have sparked an increasingly heated political and cultural fight.

article_summary:
"It's like someone had taken Miracle-Gro and all of a sudden there are scooters everywhere," said Mayor Lloyd Winnecke.
EVANSVILLE, Ind.—With engines designed to putter along under 25 miles an hour, it's hard to imagine low-powered scooters as much of a menace to society.
But as their numbers have multiplied in this Farm Belt river city, they have sparked an increasingly heated political and cultural fight.
